Carlos Sartorius






Executive Vice President, Worldwide Sales and Services
Carlos Sartorius is Executive Vice President, Worldwide Sales and Services at Citrix. His team delivers market-leading virtualization, mobility management, networking and cloud services solutions to support the mobile workspace objectives of more than 400,000 customer organizations worldwide.
Sartorius joined Citrix in 2011 as managing director and vice president of the Europe, Middle East and Africa (EMEA) organization, where he focused on accelerating revenue growth and maximizing the effectiveness of Citrix routes to market across the region. He has previously held EMEA-wide leadership roles at HP, Orange Business Services, Avaya and Motorola.
Fluent in English, German and Spanish, Sartorius earned his bachelor’s degree in electrical engineering (BSEE) with a focus on communications systems from the Universidad Iberoamericana (The Ibero-American University) in Mexico.





















 




